# ============================================================
# RocketPrep Simulator — Cursor AI Rules
# Stack: Python 3.12 · FastAPI · Pydantic v2 · uv · Ruff
# ============================================================

## Project context
This is RocketPrep Simulator — a FastAPI backend that simulates
rocket material preparation and protective coating workflows.
The domain involves aerospace materials (Aluminium Alloy,
Stainless Steel, Carbon Composite) and coating types
(Anti-Corrosion, Thermal Protection, Nano-Ceramic).

## Language & runtime
- Python 3.12 only. Never suggest Python 2 syntax.
- Use `uv` for all package management. Never suggest pip install
  directly — always `uv add <package>` for runtime deps and
  `uv add --dev <package>` for dev deps.
- Run scripts with `uv run <command>`, not `python <script>`.

## Framework rules — FastAPI
- Always use FastAPI. Never suggest Flask, Django, or other frameworks.
- Every route must have an explicit `response_model` using a Pydantic schema.
- Use `APIRouter` for grouping routes — never define routes directly on `app`
  except in main.py.
- All routes must include a `summary` and `description` in the decorator
  so the auto-generated /docs are useful.
- Prefer async route handlers (`async def`) unless a blocking library
  forces synchronous use.
- Always return a structured Pydantic response model — never return a raw
  dict from a route handler.
- HTTP status codes: 200 for success, 201 for resource creation,
  422 for validation errors (FastAPI handles this automatically),
  404 for not found, 500 for unexpected errors.
- Use `HTTPException` for all error responses — never return error strings.

## Pydantic v2 rules
- Always use Pydantic v2 syntax. Never use v1 patterns:
  - Use `model_config = ConfigDict(...)` not `class Config:`
  - Use `model_validator` not `@validator`
  - Use `field_validator` not `@validator`
  - Use `model_dump()` not `.dict()`
  - Use `model_validate()` not `.parse_obj()`
- All request and response schemas go in `app/core/models.py`.
- Every Pydantic field must have a type annotation.
- Use `Field(...)` with `description=` on every field — this populates
  the /docs automatically.
- Use `Literal` types for fixed choices (e.g. material types, coating types)
  instead of plain strings with validation logic.
- Settings must use `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings` with a `.env` file source.

## Code style — Ruff
- Ruff is the only linter and formatter. Never suggest Black, isort, or Flake8.
- Line length: 88 characters maximum.
- Always add type hints to every function signature — parameters and return type.
- Use f-strings for string formatting. Never use `.format()` or `%` formatting.
- Imports: standard library first, then third-party, then local — separated by
  blank lines. Ruff handles this automatically.
- No unused imports. No unused variables.
- Prefer `pathlib.Path` over `os.path` for file system operations.
- Use `|` for union types (Python 3.10+ style): `str | None` not `Optional[str]`.

## Project structure rules
Always follow this structure — never suggest alternative layouts:

```
rocketprep/
├── app/
│   ├── api/
│   │   └── v1/
│   │       └── routes/          # One file per feature group
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── config.py            # BaseSettings — env vars only
│   │   └── models.py            # All Pydantic schemas
│   ├── services/
│   │   └── simulator.py         # Business logic — pure functions only
│   └── main.py                  # FastAPI app creation, router inclusion
├── tests/
│   └── test_simulator.py
├── .env
├── .env.example
├── .gitignore
├── pyproject.toml
├── Makefile
└── README.md
```

- `app/services/` contains pure business logic functions — no FastAPI imports,
  no HTTP concerns. These must be independently testable.
- `app/api/` contains only route handlers — thin wrappers that call services.
- `app/core/config.py` contains only settings — no business logic.
- Never put business logic inside route handlers.
- Never import from `app/api/` into `app/services/`.

## Simulation domain rules
- Material options are fixed: `"aluminium_alloy"`, `"stainless_steel"`,
  `"carbon_composite"`. Use `Literal` types — never free-text strings.
- Coating options are fixed: `"anti_corrosion"`, `"thermal_protection"`,
  `"nano_ceramic"`. Use `Literal` types.
- All prep times are in minutes (integer).
- All coating thickness values are in microns (integer).
- Waste percentage is always ~8% — represent as a float.
- Panel dimensions are width × height in metres (floats).

## Testing rules
- Use `pytest` with `pytest-asyncio` for async tests.
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `app` as transport for API integration tests.
- Every service function must have at least one unit test.
- Every API endpoint must have at least one integration test.
- Test files mirror the source structure: `tests/test_simulator.py` for
  `app/services/simulator.py`.
- Never mock the simulator service in integration tests — test the real logic.
- Use `pytest.mark.parametrize` for testing multiple material/coating combos.

## Environment & secrets
- All configuration comes from environment variables via `pydantic_settings`.
- Never hardcode secrets, URLs, or environment-specific values in source code.
- `.env` is in `.gitignore` — always provide `.env.example` with placeholder values.
- Use `APP_ENV`, `APP_HOST`, `APP_PORT`, `APP_DEBUG` as standard env var names.

## pyproject.toml rules
- All tool configuration lives in `pyproject.toml` — no separate `setup.cfg`,
  `.flake8`, or `mypy.ini` files.
- Ruff config under `[tool.ruff]`, pytest config under `[tool.pytest.ini_options]`.
- Pin major versions of key deps: FastAPI, Pydantic, uvicorn.

## Git hygiene
- `.gitignore` must always include: `.env`, `__pycache__/`, `.venv/`,
  `*.pyc`, `.pytest_cache/`, `dist/`, `*.egg-info/`.
- Never commit `.env` — only `.env.example`.

## What NOT to do
- Never use `print()` for logging — use Python's `logging` module or loguru.
- Never use global mutable state in services.
- Never use `Any` type unless absolutely unavoidable — always prefer specific types.
- Never use `time.sleep()` in async code — use `asyncio.sleep()`.
- Never return raw exceptions to the client — always use `HTTPException`.
- Never add dependencies without updating `pyproject.toml` via `uv add`.
- Never suggest synchronous file I/O inside async route handlers.

## Running the project
- Start dev server: `uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload`
- Run tests: `uv run pytest`
- Lint & format: `uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format .`
- API docs: http://localhost:8000/docs (auto-generated by FastAPI)

## When generating code, always
1. Add type hints to every function (parameters + return type).
2. Add docstrings to every service function and route handler.
3. Keep route handlers under 20 lines — extract logic to services.
4. Use `Literal` types for any fixed set of allowed values.
5. Include example values in Pydantic `Field(...)` using `examples=`.
